[2]
Date: Wed, 03 Sep 1997 09:01:28 +1200
From: Stu MacDiarmid <macdiarmids@ra.maf.govt.nz>
So, 5 people diagnosed as having CJD reported that they has eaten squirrel
brains! I guess that just about proves it, doesn't it? Of course, I'd bet
that there are some cynics out there who might wonder whether they also drank
coffee, which, after all, is reported to exert a neuropharmacological effect
in some people. Has anybody every determined just how many CJD sufferers
drank coffee? Or how many CJD sufferers did not eat squirrel brains? In my
country there are no squirrels. We do however drink coffee and we also
report cases of CJD. Scary stuff, eh?
